Here are tips and tricks for your trouble shooting!

First check the error file, then the output file, then the log

Always start the script by entering the directory you wish the script to be executed in

The directory your output file is written to needs to exist! It will not be created for you when you run the script

peroids "." slashes "/" and dashes "-" cause the biggest crashes

pdw = current working directory
qsub = submit
qstat = status (watch qstat makes it a running log)
qdel and job ID# = kill command 

